SACRAMENTO -- Angered by the refusal of electricity wholesalers to surrender=
=20
information about suspected price gouging, a Senate committee voted Thursday=
=20
to hold two big energy companies in contempt of the Legislature.=20
It was uncertain what punishment, if any, may be in store for Enron Corp. of=
=20
Houston and Mirant Corp. of Atlanta. But committee members said potential=20
sanctions could include heavy fines and/or the jailing of corporate=20
executives.
