witnesses to Dunn. Dunn said a quick scan of the letters showed wholesalers=20
were pleading for a second chance and assuring that the subpoenaed data woul=
d=20
be forthcoming.=20
Kleinman told the committee Duke did not want to be held in contempt.=20
"We will make tens of thousands of documents available for inspection,"=20
Kleinman said.=20
But he said Duke and the committee staff still must settle on a=20
confidentiality agreement, a matter he indicated was close to resolution.=20
